Argument: Don&#x27;t use black because nothing in nature is actually black.<p>False Conclusion: Don&#x27;t use black on a web page because nothing in nature is actually black.<p>False Assumption: The black on a web page is actually pure black.<p>True Conclusion: Use black if you want to - it won&#x27;t be pure black, it will simply be the darkest you can get.<p>PS. This is also true for paint: Black paint is also not pure black.
